TITLE: Florida sheriff's deputies find 70 pounds of suspected cocaine marked '100%' floating in ocean
SUMMARY: Deputies from the Monroe County Sheriff's Office found about 70 pounds of suspected cocaine with a "100%" marking floating in the ocean on Tuesday.

TITLE: Air Force Special Operations Command grounds CV-22 Osprey aircraft over safety concerns: report
SUMMARY: The Air Force is grounding more than 50 of its CV-22 Osprey aircraft until further notice due to a number of "safety incidents" involving its clutch, a report says.

TITLE: Colorado boy, 13, dead after apparent fentanyl poisoning: family
SUMMARY: The family of a deceased Colorado eighth-grader believes he accidentally overdosed on fentanyl after potentially receiving a pill from someone at school.

TITLE: Texas man facing execution after fatally stabbing real estate agent
SUMMARY: A Dallas man is facing execution after fatally stabbing a real estate agent inside of a model home. The Texas man killed Sarah Walker in 2006.

TITLE: Las Vegas prosecutors are seeking death penalty for man accused of killing girlfriend's 4-year-old son
SUMMARY: A Las Vegas man is accused of killing his girlfriend's 4-year-old son and hiding his body in a freezer. Prosecutors plan to seek the death penalty for Brandon Lee Toseland.

TITLE: Illinois man wanted after allegedly stealing mail; USPS offers $10K reward
SUMMARY: A man is wanted in Illinois after allegedly stealing mail from a post office in Sauk Village. Authorities offered a 10,000 reward for information leading to his arrest.

TITLE: Alex Murdaugh lawyer cites Trump FBI raid in demand for evidence in murders of wife, son: 'Manufactured drama'
SUMMARY: South Carolina prosecutors ripped a press event held by Alex Murdaugh's defense lawyer, Dick Harpootlian, as "manufactured drama" over evidence on murders of Murdaugh's wife and son.

TITLE: LA County official apologizes to Vanessa Bryant in federal court
SUMMARY: A Los Angeles County official apologized Tuesday to Kobe Bryant's widow and the relative of two other victims who perished in a 2020 helicopter crash in a California courtroom.

TITLE: Kristin Smart case: California jury has questions for dog handler during trial for accused murderer
SUMMARY: Jurors overseeing the California trial for Paul and Robert Flores heard from K9 handlers enlisted to assist in the police investigation into Kristin Smart's disappearance.

TITLE: Woman in Tennessee charged with murder for slipping inmate meth 'during prison visit kiss'
SUMMARY: A Tennessee prison visitor was charged with murder for kissing an inmate during a visitation in February, which led to his overdose and death.
